Text.string: Vault Hunter! I have a mission for you. Triple-mega-priority!
I left some stuff back on Athenas!
Uh, heh—that's not about me! That's just... a song I'm writing. It's about... politics. Yeah, they're bad, right? Forget that, just find this guy before he finds my secrets!
Crap, he's tearing out pages! Pick it up, but DON'T READ ANY OF IT!

Haha, okay, okay...||“Day 11—found an alley to live in. Warm enough to survive the nights, because... there's a pressure release valve for the sewer that opens every twenty minutes.” This chick lived in a fart cave! She lost everything! Hahahaha!
Heh, okay, that was a... poem? The sewer's an allegory for... boys! Yep. Normal poem stuff. Not real. Just a made-up poem. Rrgrrgh—seriously, find this guy!

“Day 92—Got off planet, stowed away on a trade ship. Captain caught me, but we'd gone to implo so he couldn't bring me back. He's making me scrub vac suits to pay for the trip.” Ughhhh, c'mon, this is just boring exposition. Where's the farts?
Damn it, he's just throwing my... totally impersonal notes out for everyone to see! Grab 'em, Vault Hunter!

“Day 443—Captain said I could join the crew. I jumped ship at the next port, took his vac suit. Sold it for food money.” Ring, ring! Hello? We're selling attachment issues? Oh, you already have ALL of them? My bad! Hahahahaha!
No, it wasn't like that... I didn't mean to... look, SHUT UP, DUDE! Vault Hunter, listen, I'm not kidding, you have to find him, it's super important!

“Day 939—Why did I come to this dumbass monastery? All the stupid monks stink like gouda and I haven't seen any cheese since I got here! Ugh. There's one chick with blue hair I keep seeing around the market. She's got a crazy cool Maliwan gun. Maybe I can steal something from her and use it to trade for the gun.” Wuh-ohh, hope no monks are listenin'!
I am so disappointed in you, child.
I was so excited to get out of that monastery that I forgot to pack some really important stuff! You gotta get it back for me!
Brother Mendel! I didn't mean to make fun of your cheese-stink! RRAGHH, this SUCKS!
I'm just gonna skip to the end. Wait, what's this on the inside cover? A map to the key for a super secret weapon cache? Oh, cha-CHING, baby!

Argh! See, I told you there were really important notes in there! He's gonna get the key to get those guns and blow this whole place to hell! I'm sending you the location of the key—that's where he'll be! You gotta take him out!
Gahaha! Can—can you imagine? This chick is so alone! She has no one! She can't trust anyone and she LIVED IN A FART CAVE!
Rrrgh! Can you PLEASE kill this dude?!
I'm gonna need some help picking up all my cool guns. Hey, all you guys who have been absolutely lovin' these sadsack diary entries, come help me out!
Man, screw that dude for REAL. Grab that key, Vault Hunter. Those weapons aren't safe now that Maliwan knows where they're hidden, so you should probably take them.
Got the key? Kickass. The cache isn't too far away.
Phew, I'm glad those guns are in good hands now. Now, uh... could you bring all my stuff back?
Thank you! How about this—you go enjoy those weapons, and I go burn my dia... I mean notebook, and we just never mention any of this again. Cool? Cool.
That's my stuff! What the hell?! If Maliwan's taking my stuff, you gotta get it back!
Ugh, I knew I shouldn't have left stuff lying around. When I was... before I met Maya, I only held on to things I could carry or stash. Guess I thought for a second Athenas was gonna be different.
Wait, if they found all this stuff... Crap, my notebook! You have to go make sure my notebook is safe. That gets out, I'll literally die. It has all my super-secret notes!
No! Where is it?! WHO TOOK MY NOTEBOOK?!

Hey! Hey everyone! It's me, Private Beans! Quit burning people's homes down for a sec and check out this emo chick's dumb diary! It's hilarious! Here, listen! Ahem.||“Running Scared, Day 1—I think my whole family's dead and I don't know what to do.” Hahahaha! Right?
That's not—you can't—Vault Hunter, you gotta do something! Find him!

Hahaha!||“Day 3—I miss my family so much. Sometimes it feels like my heart is a fist clenched around a piece of barbed wire and it hurts so much to hold onto the wire but I'm afraid to let go of the wire because then I won't have it anymore.” Whomp whomp! Pthbthtbthb, hahahaha!
